## J. Consumer Audit (Mandatory for Interface/Config Changes)

When a plan modifies or adds parameters to any config class, data contract,
or public interface, complete this audit BEFORE implementation.

**Step 1: Identify modified interfaces**

| Modified Class/Interface | New/Changed Parameters |
|--------------------------|----------------------|
| | |

**Step 2: Search for ALL instantiation points**

For each modified class, run: `{{ config.search_command | default('rg "ClassName(" --type py') }}` and list every file.

| Class | File | Line | Already in File Impact Map? |
|-------|------|------|-----------------------------|
| | | | Yes / No (add if No) |

**Step 3: Search for ALL callers of modified functions**

| Function | Caller File | Line | Updated in Plan? |
|----------|-------------|------|--------------------|
| | | | Yes / No |

**Step 4: Verify parameter flows end-to-end**

For each new parameter, trace from entry point (CLI/config/API) to every consumer:

| Parameter | Entry Point | Intermediate Hops | Final Consumer(s) | Verified? |
|-----------|-------------|--------------------|--------------------|-----------|
| | | | | |

**Step 5: Plan integration test coverage**

| Flow Path | Test Exists? | Test Verifies New Param? |
|-----------|--------------|--------------------------|
| | | |

